        <name>vlc_interrupt_raise</name>
        <param>
          <type>vlc_interrupt_t *</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Raises an interruption through a specified context.</para>
<para>This is used to asynchronously wake a thread up while it is waiting on some other events (typically I/O events).</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>This function is thread-safe. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>This function is not a cancellation point. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
